{"published time": "2024-03-08T10-42-99", "images": ["https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fortyfikacziyi2.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fortyfikacziyi.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fortyfikacziyi3.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fortyfikacziyi4.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/fortyfikacziyi5.jpg"], "content": "<div class=\"single-content\"><figure class=\"post-thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"853\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000000.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000000.jpg\" width=\"1280\"/></figure><!-- .post-thumbnail --><p><strong>Deputy Minister of Defense of Ukraine Lieutenant General Ivan Havrylyuk drove several hundred kilometers along the front line to see at the spot at what pace the defense borders are arranged.</strong></p><p>About this<a href=\"https://t.me/ministry_of_defense_ua/9042\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">reported March 8</a>Ministry of Defence Ukraine.</p><p>\u201cObjectively, recently engineering work on the construction of defense lines has been rapid. For several weeks, this is facilitated by the weather. New forces and technical capabilities are involved. The government has allocated the necessary funds, \u201dIvan Havrylyuk said.</p><div class=\"fotorama--wp\" data-auto=\"false\" data-captiontag=\"dd\" data-columns=\"0\" data-icontag=\"dt\" data-ids=\"549205,549206,549207,549208\" data-itemtag=\"dl\" data-link=\"file\" data-max-width=\"100%\" data-ratio=\"1.5005861664713\" data-size=\"large\" data-width=\"1280\"><div class=\"gallery galleryid-549201 gallery-columns-0 gallery-size-thumbnail\" id=\"gallery-1\"><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon landscape\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000001.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000001.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon landscape\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000002.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000002.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon landscape\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000003.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000003.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon landscape\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000004.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-08T10-42-99/000004.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl></div></div><p>According to him, the plan of fortification of defense borders, which defines the volume of work, terms of execution and responsible for each section, was drawn up and approved.</p><p>Earlier the issue of strengthening fortification<a href=\"https://armyinform.com.ua/2023/11/28/prezydent-proviv-stavku-verhovnogo-golovnokomanduvacha-posylennya-fortyfikacziyi-mobilnyh-vognevyh-grup-ta-robotu-ppo/\">was considered</a>At the meeting of the Supreme Commander.</p></div>", "source": "https://armyinform.com.ua/2024/03/08/ivan-gavrylyuk-roboty-z-budivnycztva-linij-oborony-vedutsya-pryskorenymy-tempamy/", "title": "Ivan Havrylyuk: Defense Line Construction Work is at an accelerated pace", "description": "This was reported on March 8 by the Ministry of Defense of Ukraine. \u201cObjectively, lately ...", "author": ["Army Inform"], "categories": ["\u0412\u0430\u0436\u043b\u0438\u0432\u043e", "\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438"], "tags": ["\u0406\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0413\u0430\u0432\u0440\u0438\u043b\u044e\u043a", "\u0444\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0456 \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0434\u0438"]}